	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, May 14th 2:23 AM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=144304><span id= >Monyetman</span></a><br><span id=notbold>16 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [1.60]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Look i have played both mage and druid to lvl 52 and these are the things i have found.<br><br>Solo : Mage wins. I went from level 30 to 39 in 4 days playing roughly 3 hours a day soloing the WR and RR (RR from 34+) in HHK. Name me a druid who can do that? then from 50 to 52 i chain pulled seafurys and killing gornit whenever he popped WITHOUT ANY MED BREAKS. I killed constantly for 4 hours doing that, never going below 80% mana unless i felt like nuking their @sses off. name me a druid who can do that? My druid consisted of - quad kite, med for 5 mins, quad kite, med for 5 mins. jeeeeeez so much med so damn BORING thats why i stopped playing him.<br><br>Group : Again mage wins. Druid nukes at level 52 - 612 dmg. Mage nuke - 980 dmg. Plus pet... constant damage yadda yadda yadda. By that stage nobody is going to want a druid for healing. i mean come on superior heal in planes when mobs are hitting for 200+ anyway? By that stage the only healers that are wanted are clerics and shamans - shaman slow kinda acts as a heal, but once people group with a mage they see how much dps we put out, AND we can tailor our pets to any situation.<br><br>So what happens? Mages drop druids like a hot potato, as do groups. <br><br>Magefyre Stormflyte<br>52 Elementalist of Morell Thule<br><br>Muluven Canabellum<br>52 Wanderer of Morell Thule</p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
